The paper deals with the convergence of a multi-agent system, which is a topic that falls under the category of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA). The use of gradient descent and control laws for neighboring agents suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of Control Systems (cs.SY) and Robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of partitions, which is a topic that falls under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper's focus on convergence and optimization suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
